line_1: Thus He who runs or dances, begs
line_2: The equal Vigor of Two Legs:

line_1: The ogling Youth most humbly begs,
line_2: With down-cast Looks on Totta's Legs,

line_1: And his Money still wastes, till he starves or he begs.
line_2: The Cloaths that hang on him are turning to Rags:

line_1: My awkart Muse sair pleads and begs,
My awkart Muse sair pleads and begs,
line_2: Rattlin the corn out-owre the rigs,

line_1: My awkart Muse sair pleads and begs,
line_2: Or dealing thro' amang the naigs
